        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer6637746" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15411719045352701178">Upon 2nd reading of this book, I realized that any form of negativity I may have in the moment actually reflects a resistance to the present moment - a refusal to accept the here and now (which is the only reality).<br/><br/>Previous to this, I had thought that negativity simply is - and therefore should simply be noticed and accepted as part of the current reality, and not struggled against.<br/><br/>True, negativity shouldn&apos;t be railed at nor struggled against - but should instead be simply noticed. And noticing </span>
  <span id="freeText15411719045352701178" style="display:none">Upon 2nd reading of this book, I realized that any form of negativity I may have in the moment actually reflects a resistance to the present moment - a refusal to accept the here and now (which is the only reality).<br /><br />Previous to this, I had thought that negativity simply is - and therefore should simply be noticed and accepted as part of the current reality, and not struggled against.<br /><br />True, negativity shouldn't be railed at nor struggled against - but should instead be simply noticed. And noticing negativity includes awareness that it involves my resistance to the here and now, and my choosing instead to be wrapped up in my thoughts - and that there is a liberating alternative that is actually what is true and real.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15411719045352701178" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
