</a><br>(Throwback Review) Elkhart Tolle is a German-born spiritual teacher and author. In this book, he tells us about enlightenment by spiritual awakening. He tells us the importance of focusing on the current moment without overthinking about the past and the future.<br><i><blockquote><b> “Time isn’t precious at all, because it is an illusion. What you perceive as precious is not time but the one point that is out of time: the Now. That is precious indeed. The more you are focused on time—past and future—the more you miss the Now, the most precious thing there is.” </b></blockquote> </i></span>
